Rishi Sunak is expected to announce that the wage-subsidy scheme for furloughed workers will be scaled back from July as the government looks at gradually lifting lockdown measures. We want to hear about your experiences and how you feel about the expected announcement. What has it been like being furloughed? Have you had any problems receiving payments? Do you have any concerns for the future? What do you think of the government’s suggestion that the country is “addicted” to wage-subsidies? You can get in touch by filling in the form below. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact for publication before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.